{
  // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  // RZCUSTOMLOOT
  //
  // Items are injected directly into PMC pockets AFTER the bot is fully generated, bypassing SPT's loot budget and weight system entirely.
  // This guarantees deterministic drops unlike the pool-weight approach.
  //
  // HOW IT WORKS - SEQUENTIAL FILLING:
  //   Items are processed in order, top to bottom.
  //   For each item:
  //     1. A chance roll is performed (0–100).
  //     2. If the roll FAILS → the item is skipped, the slot is NOT consumed, and we move on to the next item in the list.
  //     3. If the roll PASSES → the item is injected into the next free slot.
  //   We stop when all pocket slots are full OR the list is exhausted.
  //
  // SLOT COUNT:
  //   Standard PMC pockets have 4 slots (pocket1 → pocket4).
  //   The mod reads the actual pocket template from the DB at runtime, so
  //   extended pockets (boss pockets, quest reward pockets, etc.) are handled
  //   automatically — no hardcoded limit.
  //
  // ITEM ORDER MATTERS:
  //   Items at the top of the list are prioritized. If pockets are already partially filled by SPT's normal loot generation,
  //   lower-priority items may not fit. Put your most important items first.
  //
  // ONLY USE 1x1 ITEMS:
  //   Pocket slots are individual grid cells, not a 2D container.
  //   Large items (2x1, 1x2, etc.) will NOT fit and may cause client issues.
  //
  // CHANCE:
  //   0   = never drops (same as setting enabled: false)
  //   50  = drops roughly half the time
  //   100 = always drops (guaranteed, injected every time)
  //   A failed roll does NOT block subsequent items — the slot stays free.
  // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  // Master switch - enable/disable all features.
  "Enabled": true,

